OL,3,CViolent crimes against women on
OL,4,CBritain's trains jump by more than 50%
OL,6,FThe number of sexual offences jumped
OL,7,F10% over the same period, while sexual
OL,8,Fharassment reports doubled, the data
OL,9,Ffirst reported by The Times also
OL,10,Frevealed.
OL,12,FA separate British Transport Police
OL,13,F(BTP) survey released last year
OL,14,Freported more than a third of all
OL,15,Fwomen travelling by rail would be
OL,16,Fassaulted during their commute.
OL,18,FBTP data also indicates that most
OL,19,Fassaults occur during the evening rush
OL,20,Fhour when trains are packed and busy.
