OL,6,F"If we see something that isn't right,
OL,7,Fdoing something about it, whether
OL,8,Fthat's intervening, if you feel safe
OL,9,Fto do so or reporting it to police."
OL,11,FMinister for Safeguarding and Violence
OL,12,FAgainst Women and Girls, Jess
OL,13,FPhillips, said the latest figures need
OL,14,Fto be taken "incredibly seriously".
OL,16,F"There is just a continuing trend of
OL,17,Fwomen being under attack whether
OL,18,Fthat's in their homes, on buses, on
OL,19,Ftrains, or as they go about their
